result.name: Mean Noodles 麵佬到

reviews.text:
I wasn’t really experienced with Malaysian foods so it was a bit hard to comprehend the taste. But definitely felt that it is not your regular noodle. The broth had a very deep taste with many toppings which made in overall a very delicate experience.
Very friendly staffs!
The price was a bit expensive though....
Uniquely featured menus and interior furnishings. Tasty soup base and fresh ingredients for noodles. Haven’t tried their cocktails. Trust it’s quite an experience as a bar in the nighttime

Hidden little noodle bar in Sheung Wan that serves Malaysian delicacies. Loved the Char Kway Teow and the Laksa Battered Wings- which unfortunately arrived after my main course due to my server punching in the wrong order.

The food & interior is spot on but a tiny bit more attentiveness would've been great!

p.s. If you're having trouble finding the place, it's in the alleyway behind Yardbird.
Loved how they did the char kway teow!
Take a wander down a little lane behind the Western Market to discover this genuine gem. Fresh laksa herbs and ingredients flown in from Malaysia.
